<br>
1) Pick your avatar as follows: its width cannot exceed 130 pixels, and its height cannot exceed 150 pixels. It must also meet the file size limitations that the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>file size of your avatar and all images in your signatures should not exceed 40KB,</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> as stated in the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm18.showMessage?topicID=7.topic">Board Rules</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. Finally, please do not use images that contain rapid flashing or similar eye sores.<br>
<br>
2) Get your image online on a host that allows outside file linking. All the information you need to do this can be found <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm27.showMessage?topicID=19.topic">in this FAQ for people familiar with websites and hosting</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> and <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.7hat.com/posting/">getting images online for beginners</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br>
<br>
3) <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/BBSUser.fromWeb?boardName=polykarbonbbs&amp;back=polykarbonbbs&amp;language=EN">Click Here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> or visit &quot;My Control Center&quot; from PK BBS's main page. Go to &quot;Edit Profile&quot;, and the first field you'll see is My Photo. Uncheck the &quot;private&quot; box, and enter the URL of your avatar in the text field below. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>To resize your avatar, after the image URL in the same field, type the following:<br>
<br>
height=100 width=100</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Replace the numbers with the dimensions of your image, but remember the size restriction I mentioned earlier. When you view your profile, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>your avatar will display as a broken link in your profile.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Don't worry, if you typed it right, it will display fine when you post!<br>
<br>
Paying members can get rid of the broken image in your profile simply by removing it. To do this, just paste this into your CSC box when editing your profile:<br>
<br>
#personalphoto{display:none}<br>
<br>
